cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.MM, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the diffusion of trends in online social media and the role of the crowd and opinion leaders in this process.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper may discuss the development of algorithms or tools for analyzing social media data.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the societal implications of the findings for marketing practice and influence maximization in social networks.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the use of multimedia content (e.g. memes) in the diffusion of trends in online social media.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze social media data.
